=Configure the Cr-48 Keyboard in Windows= 

----
==== ==== 
====Follow this guide to configure the Cr-48 keyboard to function correctly in Windows.==== 
# ====Install Windows 7 by following the guide [[Windows7|here]], or Windows 8 by following the guide [[Windows8|here]].==== 
# ====Download and install [[http://www.autohotkey.com/download/|AutoHotkey]]==== 
** During installation, select the "Unicode (32-bit)" version
# ====Run AutoHotkey==== 
** The first time AutoHotkey runs, a sample script is created in the Notepad application
** Erase the contents of the sample script and paste the custom script for the Cr-48 keyboard available [[http://automatedme.googlecode.com/svn-history/r180/AutoHotKey/cr-48.ahk|here]]
** Save the script and exit Notepad
# ====Place a shortcut to the AutoHotkey application in the Startup folder. Instructions for this step are available [[http://windows.microsoft.com/en-US/windows-xp/help/setup/run-programs-at-startup|here]]==== 
# ====Restart the computer==== 

Source: [[http://code.google.com/p/automatedme/]]

